@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="section-frame policy-shell">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
            <div class="eyebrow">Privacy</div>
            <h1 class="page-title">Privacy for a collaboration-first workspace.</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="section-copy">
            This project separates authentication, document storage, and collaboration services so account access and document state remain explicit.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-grid">
        <article class="editorial-card">
            <div class="card-kicker">Identity</div>
            <h2>Accounts are handled through ASP.NET Core Identity.</h2>
            <p>Authentication state is managed in the MVC client and tied to your collaboration context.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="editorial-card">
            <div class="card-kicker">Documents</div>
            <h2>Shared content follows role-based access rules.</h2>
            <p>Owners, editors, and viewers receive different levels of access across document workflows and invite states.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="editorial-card">
            <div class="card-kicker">Realtime</div>
            <h2>Presence and sync are scoped to active documents.</h2>
            <p>Collaboration updates are delivered through SignalR and revision-aware APIs rather than broad client trust.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>
